[SN]TITLE[SN]
European Rugby Challenge Cup: Gloucester 37-8 Benetton Treviso

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Gloucester kept up their perfect record in the Challenge Cup with a comfortable bonus-point win over Benetton Treviso.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Greig Laidlaw kicked two penalties before Lewis Ludlow went over as Gloucester led 13-0 after 25 minutes.
Ian McKinley's penalty was the Italian side's first points before Jonny May went over at the end of the first half.
Michael Tagicakibau's got a try for Treviso soon after the break, but Matt Scott got a third soon after before Callum Barley's late fourth.
Gloucester: Hook; Sharples, Scott, Twelvetrees, May; Burns, Laidlaw (c); McAllister, Matu'u, Afoa, Savage, Latta, Moriarty, Kvesic, Ludlow.
Replacements: Hibbard, Orr, Ma'afu, Clarke, Rowan, Braley, Atkinson, Thorley.
